<section class="section section-light">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="center">
      <div class="section-badge">Pricing FAQ</div>
      <h2 class="section-headline">Answers to common questions.</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="faq-list">
      <div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q">How does pricing work?</div><div class="faq-a">Essentials and Professional start through self-serve signup. Enterprise is sales-led because larger deployments typically require security review, procurement, SSO planning, and custom rollout support.</div></div>
      <div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q">What's the minimum seat count?</div><div class="faq-a">Essentials starts at 50 seats. Professional starts at 100 seats. Enterprise is custom. If you're below the minimums, reach out anyway.</div></div>
      <div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q">Is there an annual commitment required?</div><div class="faq-a">The published pricing is for annual billing. Monthly billing is available at a 20% premium. Multi-year agreements receive additional discounts.</div></div>
      <div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q">What tools does Cadence replace?</div><div class="faq-a">Cadence Essentials targets 1:1 management, AI meeting summaries, manager-lane AI coaching, goals, recognition, pulse-survey response collection, and Job Architecture workflows. Professional adds ER case management, Culture Scorecard visibility, employee-lane AI coaching, 9-box calibration, Personality Intelligence (consented working-style profiles and team view), and Connected Agents (bring-your-own-AI over MCP with audit logging). Enterprise adds OIDC and SAML SSO plus configurable retention. Turnover prediction, full survey campaign management, personality signal woven into 1:1s, SCIM provisioning, and role-recasting workflows remain preview, planning, or roadmap items.</div></div>
      <div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q">Do you offer a free trial?</div><div class="faq-a">Yes. Essentials starts with a free trial through the live signup funnel. Professional checkout starts from the same signup path.</div></div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section-cta">
  <div class="container">
    <h2>Ready to consolidate your stack?</h2>
    <p>Tell us about your org and we'll build a consolidation model showing exactly what you'd replace and what you'd save.</p>
    <div class="btn-group" style="justify-content:center;">
      <a href="https://app.cadencehr.ai/signup?tier=essentials&intent=self-serve&source=apex-pricing-cta" class="btn btn-white btn-lg">Start free trial</a>
      <a href="mailto:demo@cadencehr.ai?subject=Pricing%20question" class="btn btn-white-outline btn-lg">Talk to us</a>
